 Two men will appear in court soon after they were arrested on Thursday for possession of dagga in Lusikisiki. According to a police spokesperson, Captain Handile, the dagga had a combined worth of R6 400 on the street. “The two men, aged 28 and 18 years old, were arrested for possession of dagga weighing 2,6kg with the street value of R2 600 as well as more dagga weighing 3,8 kg with the street value of R3 800.” According to a police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha, early on Friday morning, another man was arrested at Mntla Locality, at Mtebhele Village, in Ngqamakhwe, also for possession of dagga. The dagga has a street value of R1 500. 